{"source":"LEETCODE","id":"106","title":"Construct Binary Tree from Inorder and Postorder Traversal","description":"\u003cp\u003eGiven two integer arrays \u003ccode\u003einorder\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003epostorder\u003c/code\u003e where \u003ccode\u003einorder\u003c/code\u003e is the inorder traversal of a binary tree and \u003ccode\u003epostorder\u003c/code\u003e is the postorder traversal of the same tree, construct and return \u003cem\u003ethe binary tree\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong class\u003d\"example\"\u003eExample 1:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cimg alt\u003d\"\" src\u003d\"https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2021/02/19/tree.jpg\" style\u003d\"width: 277px; height: 302px;\" /\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eInput:\u003c/strong\u003e inorder \u003d [9,3,15,20,7], postorder \u003d [9,15,7,20,3]\n\u003cstrong\u003eOutput:\u003c/strong\u003e [3,9,20,null,null,15,7]\n\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong class\u003d\"example\"\u003eExample 2:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eInput:\u003c/strong\u003e inorder \u003d [-1], postorder \u003d [-1]\n\u003cstrong\u003eOutput:\u003c/strong\u003e [-1]\n\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConstraints:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e1 \u0026lt;\u003d inorder.length \u0026lt;\u003d 3000\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003epostorder.length \u003d\u003d inorder.length\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e-3000 \u0026lt;\u003d inorder[i], postorder[i] \u0026lt;\u003d 3000\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003einorder\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003epostorder\u003c/code\u003e consist of \u003cstrong\u003eunique\u003c/strong\u003e values.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eEach value of \u003ccode\u003epostorder\u003c/code\u003e also appears in \u003ccode\u003einorder\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003einorder\u003c/code\u003e is \u003cstrong\u003eguaranteed\u003c/strong\u003e to be the inorder traversal of the tree.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003epostorder\u003c/code\u003e is \u003cstrong\u003eguaranteed\u003c/strong\u003e to be the postorder traversal of the tree.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","difficulty":"Medium","timeLimit":"","memoryLimit":"","contestProbId":"construct-binary-tree-from-inorder-and-postorder-traversal","parameterNames":["inorder","postorder"],"testCases":[{"input":"[9,3,15,20,7]\n[9,15,7,20,3]","expectedOutput":"[3,9,20,null,null,15,7]"},{"input":"[-1]\n[-1]","expectedOutput":"[-1]"}]}